snippet.textDisplay:
There is something everyone seems to be misunderstanding, Jenny said she uses real Swarovski crystals which is a man made stone. Swarovski is a brand name for a range of precision-cut crystal GLASS so its susceptible to scratches and chipping from wear and tear. When she refers to using the crystal itself she’s referring to the brand of crystal used. Swarovski crystals are divided into different types (groups) according to their usage. The main types of Swarovski crystals are: beads, pendants, round stones, buttons and so on. Of course they aren’t sending loose crystals of the same quality as you’d be purchasing in store for a service that is only meant to last a few weeks and if you thought you were getting a hand full of aged crystals for only $700?! Oh honey 🤦🏽‍♀️
I think you should of done more research before coming on here and bashing the integrity of her work. You nails look great btw!

snippet.textDisplay:
As a watch and jewellery specialist myself, I thought I’d share my opinion, I believe They’re branded under Swarovski, however the “Jewell’s” can be bought on eBay the main center one pricing between £4-£8.

https://rover.ebay.com/rover/0/0/0?mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.co.uk%2Fulk%2Fitm%2F322012833921

Swarovski do different types of stones too, these being crystals, Diamonds & Cubic zirconia.

The girls in the store will be trained around ONLY jewellery, rather than the vast selection of items people customise, therefore they can only compare it to that.

I bought a Swarovski brow band for my horses bridle a few years back, it cost me £18, Of course these stones need to be more durable than the diamonds or crystals placed in jewellery, and therefore could and would not compare to diamond or jewellery in a store (UNDER SPECIALIST LIGHTING BTW)

I don’t think she’s been openly lying I simply believe she’s either buying fake “crystals”believing they’re real, or Swarovski cater in party rhinestones, used for nails and trainers too.

PLEASE BE AWARE SWAROVSKI CRYSTALS ARE MAN-MADE AND EXTREMELY OVERPRICED FOR QUALITY.
